vision.notes: Presumed to be well-developed, as they are owls. Owl vision is typically adapted for nocturnal hunting, with large eyes for light gathering and potentially good binocular vision for depth perception.

hearing.notes: Presumed to have good hearing, similar to modern owls, which is crucial for detecting prey. This may include adaptations for sound localization.

tactile.notes: Likely possess tactile senses similar to modern birds, used for detecting prey and navigating their environment.

olfaction.notes: Olfactory capabilities are unknown, but are likely similar to modern owls. Owls do not rely as much on scent compared to many other bird groups.
